'''The Master SME'''

We use an idea called M-SME (Master Subject Matter Expert) to help in the development of technical training.  This M-SME is typically a retired generalist that is experienced in the technical subject matter, but is not an expert on any individual area.  After the Instuctional Designers meet with the individual SMEs, the M-SME can help clarify content issues without taking up the SMEs valuable time.  This method allows one M-SME to be the single goto point with the designers so the individual SME does not need to get bogged down in the details of the development.  Similarly, the M-SME can go to the individual SME to get clarification on a technical point in a much smoother fashion than the non-technical ID or Technical Writer could.

{{BookCat}}

Training games and activities are fantastic ways for a trainer to make the training fun and interactive. There are many different games and activities one can engage in during the training. 

The website of Sivasailam "Thiagi" Thiagarajan, who uses games and activities extensively in his training programs, has [http://www.thiagi.com/games.html a large amount of game ideas].

{{BookCat}}

See [[w:User:jwilkinson|my user page]] over on wikipedia.


