{{ingredient}}

Frikadelle, are the South African version of meatballs.
Made of ground beef, ostrich, lamb, fish, pork, or veal, onions, eggs, salt and pepper, these are formed into balls and flattened somewhat. They are then pan-fried in butter, margarine or even vegetable oil.

